%25 ''Madam Sweet of %25color=#9e0b0f%25 The The Invictus'' %25%25--][[%3c%3c]]%0a> [--%25color=#585858%25 ''Gangrel'' %25%25--][[%3c%3c]]%0a> (:tableend:)%0a> [[%3c%3c]]%0a> %0a> [[%3c%3c]]%0a> (:table border=0 style=float width=100%25 align=center cellspacing=5 cellpadding=2 :)%0a> (:cellnr Calign=center valign=bottom:)%0a> %25cframe width=150px bgcolor=#95ABB8%25 %25width=150%25http://amourdelavie.net/schreier/maintop.jpg%0a> (:cell Calign=center valign=bottom:)%0a> %25cframe width=150px bgcolor=#95ABB8%25 %25width=150%25http://i490.photobucket.com/albums/rr261/milokoplus/witch_zpse3ca558c.jpg%0a> (:cell Calign=center valign=bottom:)%0a> (:cellnr align=center:)%0a> [-%25color=#9e0b0f%25 [[Jackson Barrett]]%25%25-]\\%0a> [--%25color=#585858%25 ''Speaker'' %25%25--][[%3c%3c]]%0a> [--%25color=#585858%25 ''Mister Speaker of%25color=#9e0b0f%25 The Invictus'' %25%25--][[%3c%3c]]%0a> [--%25color=#585858%25 ''Ventrue'' %25%25--][[%3c%3c]]%0a> (:cell align=center:)%0a> [-%25color=#9e0b0f%25 [[Ashildr De Haviland]]%25%25-]\\%0a> [--%25color=#585858%25 ''Notary'' %25%25--][[%3c%3c]]%0a> [--%25color=#585858%25 ''Madam Notary %25color=#9e0b0f%25 the Invictus'' %25%25--][[%3c%3c]]%0a> [--%25color=#585858%25 ''Nosferatu'' %25%25--][[%3c%3c]]%0a> (:tableend:)%0a> [[%3c%3c]]%0a> %0a> [[%3c%3c]]%0a> %0a> (:table valign=top:)%0a> (:cellnr colspan=3 width=380 bgcolor=#9e0b0f align=center:)%0a> !!%25Black%25[+Charter+]%25Black%25%0a> (:table border=0 style=float width=100%25 align=center cellspacing=5 cellpadding=2 :)%0a> (:cellnr Calign=center valign=bottom:)%0a> %0a> ''%25color=#9e0b0f%25Formal Charter of the Savannah Chapter of the Most Noble Order of the Fallen King%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25''''+Mission+''''%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25The Most Noble Order of the Fallen King (the Order) has been established to protect and further the interests of the Invictus of Savannah, Georgia (the Invictus). This will include both personally protecting members and resources of the Covenant, as well as training other members to protect themselves.%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25''''+Organization+''''%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25The Order is organized as a martial guild under the umbrella organization of the Invictus. The Order follows a strict hierarchy, although the only required position is the Knight Commander. Other positions are created and filled as qualified individuals join the order and needs arise. All members of the order are expected to protect and serve the Invictus to the best of their abilities, accepting requests of any Invictus in good standing. The positions and their primary responsibilities are:%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25'+'''Knight Commander'''+'%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Leader of Martial Guild/Chapter.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Act as the Representative of the Order to the Inner Council of the Invictus.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Approve all inductions and promotions within the Order.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Meet with important Invictus Clients.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Act as Final Arbiter of disputes within the Order.%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25'+'''Knight Captain'''+'%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Organize and oversee training of Knights, Squires and Clients.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Personally lead missions of strategic importance.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Act as Arbiter of minor disputes within the Order.%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25'+'''Knight'''+'%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Train squires and other clients in the martial guild.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Collect payments from Clients for completed or cancelled tasks.%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25'+'''Knight Errant'''+'%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Probationary position given to a Knight under discipline.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Held to the standards of a Knight but given the responsibility and authority of a Squire.%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25'+'''Squire'''+'%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Train and learn the ways of knighthood%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Assist Knights in any tasks they might have%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Prepare for initiation into the Invictus if not already a member%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-NOTE: May leave the Order at any time though will be banned from attempting to join any form of Knighthood in the future%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25'+'''Support'''+'%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25In addition to its members, the Order has supporters that assist with its operations. This includes but is not limited to financial management, operational support, and logistical administration. These supporters are allies of the Order but are not members. Depending on the individuals role and level of support, these individuals may be given honorary titles. Not that an individual may have both a function and patronage title associated with the Order:%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Function:%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Advisor%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-A close advisor and trusted confidant of the Knight Commander. %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Patronage:%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Patron%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-The highest level of support. These individuals have significant responsibilities to the Order and are given the greatest level of respect.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Benefactor%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-A significant contributor to the Order. These individuals may provide financial support to the Order or provide other services.%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25''''+Location+''''%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25The Order will be housed in the the building at 651 East Broughton Street, in the Bay Side District (http://goo.gl/maps/I56Ab). This building, made of heavy brick with all of the windows boarded up, serves as the Order’s base of operations. Training is conducted on the main floor and the adjacent barn and grounds. The second floor is used as office space and to meet with potential and current clients. The basement serves as a barracks and lounge area for members and clients. The top floors are reserved for the exclusive use of Knight Commander and his or her advisors. %0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25'+'''Clients'''+'%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25The Order fulfills its purpose by serving its Clients. All members of the Invictus in good standing will automatically be accepted as clients of the Order. Those not of the Invictus may be accepted as Clients, but this is at the sole discretion of the Knight Commander. There are certain expectations that the Order holds its Clients to:%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Present the Order with tasks appropriate and worthy of the Order.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Insignificant or insulting tasks from members of the Invictus will be performed but Client may face reprisal at the discretion of the Knight Commander.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Repeated insults to the Order by a Client will result in the Client being denied further services.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Provide Compensation to the Order.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Payment is required once the task is accepted, unless the Order fails to complete the task.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Payment is required even if Client later cancels the task.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Payment should be fair considering the task.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Client is NOT required to describe the anticipated payment at time of presenting the task.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-May petition to train at the Martial guild.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Payment or trade equal to the value of the training is expected.%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25'+'''Compensation'''+'%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-The Order should recommend to Clients to settle the issue of compensation before formally requesting the assistance of the Order.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Clients are not required to settle compensation before but accept the risks of not setting terms in advance.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-The Order may request an adjustment to the compensation after completion of the task if the parameters set at the agreement were incorrect or misleading.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-The Client is not required to adjust payment, but could face consequences for refusing.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Compensation is expected to be in line with what would be received for a similar task on an open market. %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Sufficiency of payment is to be determined by the Knight Commander.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-All compensation is paid to the Order, not to individual members.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-The Knight Commander may, as he or she sees fit, reward individual members with some or all of the compensation received for a task.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-The preferred method of payment is untraceable funds.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Non-financial compensation may be accepted and will be valued at the fair market value of the item or service.%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25'+'''Membership Requirements'''+'%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Potential members must join as Squires for a period of not less than 6 months.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Knight Commander may make exceptions at his or her discretion.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-All potential members must either be a member of the Invictus or unaligned.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-All members of Knight rank or higher must be members of the Invictus.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Squires are expected to work towards membership of the Invictus.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Members of other Covenants may be accepted upon renunciation of allegiance to the other Covenant.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-All Clans are accepted, but preference is given to those of Nosferatu blood.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-NOTE: A Judex may require service as punishment for an infraction against the Invictus. The punished will be accepted within the Order as a Squire and will serve in that role, with all of the opportunities and responsibilities associated with it.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-NOTE: Childer of Knights are expected to join.%0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25''''+Discipline+''''%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Failure to complete a task due to incompetence.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Demotion to probationary position of 'Knight-Errant'.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Functionally the same as a Squire.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-May be returned to full status only by Knight Commander.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Abandonment of duties.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Torpored and imprisoned for a time based on Crime.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Violence against the Invictus outside of Monomacy.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Minor instances: Demotion to 'Knight Errant.’%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Major instances: Expulsion and sent to Judex.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Refusal to follow Orders or take a legitimate task from a Invictus.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Minor Instances: Probationary status.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Maintain current rank but on notice that additional issues could result in more serious sanctions.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Major Instances: Demotion to ‘Knight Errant’ or Expulsion.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Betrayal of Order.%0a> %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-Expulsion, detainment, and sent to Judex for judgment with the Order acting as witness against the conduct of the former member.''%0a> %0a> %0a> [[%3c%3c]]%0a> (:table valign=top:)%0a> (:cellnr colspan=3 width=380 bgcolor=#9e0b0f align=center:)%0a> !!%25black%25[+The Guild+]%25black%25%0a> (:cellnr rowspan=15 width=400 align=center:) %0a>  %0a> %25color=#9e0b0f%25-The guild is still being worked on!''%0a> %0a> [[%3c%3c]]%0a> (:include CityBook.VampireNavigationBar:)%0a\ No newline at end of file%0a
